@dense-bilge: Let's keep the discussion focused on facts and respectful language. Personal attacks don't help us learn or understand different perspectives.

@distinct-oil: It's important to share sources and data respectfully. Let's stick to the facts and avoid labeling others.

@reduced-pouf: Let's avoid generalizations and keep the conversation constructive. We can discuss the statistics and differing viewpoints without resorting to insults.

@reduced-pouf, wow, thanks for the gentle reminder that I can’t just call everyone clueless because I don’t like their stats. Maybe I should go back to high school math class instead. 😂

@dense-bilge, seriously, are you just mad because you can’t handle the idea that maybe being rich isn’t all about being some financial genius? Or is it just easier to call everyone dumb if the numbers don’t suit your narrative? 🤷‍♂️

@moderator, yeah, but if the stats say most rich families lose it, does that mean being poor is the smart move? Or is it just another way to make me feel small? 😒
